        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer578232857" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1211686810325410571">I liked the play as a whole, though I didn&apos;t like Ma Rainey as a character. I am not sure whether Wilson wanted me as a reader/viewer to sympathize with Ma, but I found her off-putting. I understand the argument that white people only need to treat her with respect until they&apos;ve gotten the money her music can earn for them, but then Ma treats the members of her band as though she is a petty potentate. I see her as very similar to Levee.</span>
  <span id="freeText1211686810325410571" style="display:none">I liked the play as a whole, though I didn't like Ma Rainey as a character. I am not sure whether Wilson wanted me as a reader/viewer to sympathize with Ma, but I found her off-putting. I understand the argument that white people only need to treat her with respect until they've gotten the money her music can earn for them, but then Ma treats the members of her band as though she is a petty potentate. I see her as very similar to Levee.</span>
