<div id="review_1117008469" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1117008469" />
    <a title="Jamie Howison" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15857806-jamie-howison"><img alt="Jamie Howison" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1444960947p2/15857806.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1117008469?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jamie Howison" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jamie Howison" href="/user/show/15857806-jamie-howison">Jamie Howison</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780613364911" href="/book/show/6433819-ma-rainey-s-black-bottom">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1117008469" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5148203642014862884">I now really want to see this play! Wilson packs so many layers of the blues story into his text, meaning that he is actually dealing with layers of the African-American story; from the tensions experienced by black musicians working in a world dominated by white record companies and music publishers, to the challenges and cultural developments that came as people moved from the deep south and into northern cities. There&apos;s also a sort of picture of the way in which blues and jazz music developed</span>
  <span id="freeText5148203642014862884" style="display:none">I now really want to see this play! Wilson packs so many layers of the blues story into his text, meaning that he is actually dealing with layers of the African-American story; from the tensions experienced by black musicians working in a world dominated by white record companies and music publishers, to the challenges and cultural developments that came as people moved from the deep south and into northern cities. There's also a sort of picture of the way in which blues and jazz music developed, often in ways that left an older generation alienated by the directions taken by the younger innovators... and the younger innovators in a position of failing to draw from the wisdom and experience of those who'd cut the musical path. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5148203642014862884" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


