              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11992652200892067923">The third of the Century Cycle and just as much a gut-punch of genius as the first two. My only question was that I thought that all of the plays revolved around the Hill District of Pittsburgh. But this one takes place in Chicago. The inexorable conclusions of these plays, which is the major consistency plot-wise, is like watching the most powerful and beautiful locomotive you&apos;ve ever seen coming at you while your foot is caught in the rail.</span>
  <span id="freeText11992652200892067923" style="display:none">The third of the Century Cycle and just as much a gut-punch of genius as the first two. My only question was that I thought that all of the plays revolved around the Hill District of Pittsburgh. But this one takes place in Chicago. The inexorable conclusions of these plays, which is the major consistency plot-wise, is like watching the most powerful and beautiful locomotive you've ever seen coming at you while your foot is caught in the rail.</span>
